    "dd1362": [
      {
        "id": 1,
        "lang": "lg-nolan",
        "value": "<p>Manages the extraction of text from PDF files (not OCR) used for publication searches.</p><p>Adds the page number for easy location of articles or parts of the document.</p><p>To work, it requires the installation of a daemon like 'pdftotext', whose path is defined in the config as 'PDF_AUTOMATIC_TRANSCRIPTION_ENGINE' and is usually: '/usr/bin/pdftotext'.</p><p>More information about automatic transcription engine using XPDF from http://www.foolabs.com/xpdf/ or https://pdftot</p>"
      }
    ],
